The article is a statement made by the President on the 30th anniversary of the peace treaty between Egypt and Israel. The President acknowledges the historic event and emphasizes that peace is always possible, even in seemingly impossible conflicts. The success of Prime Minister Begin, President Sadat, and President Carter at Camp David demonstrated that progress can be achieved through communication and cooperation. The President honors the courage and foresight of these leaders and highlights the need to expand peace among Arabs and Israelis, drawing inspiration from the achievements of Israel and Egypt three decades ago.